CREATE TABLE robot_calibration_data (
  robot_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  calibration_date DATE,
  calibration_type VARCHAR(50),
  calibration_value FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE robot_model (
  model_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  model_name VARCHAR(50),
  manufacturer VARCHAR(50),
  production_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE calibration_engineer (
  engineer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  engineer_name VARCHAR(50),
  engineer_email VARCHAR(50),
  engineer_phone VARCHAR(15)
)

CREATE TABLE calibration_history (
  history_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  robot_id INT,
  calibration_date DATE,
  calibration_engineer_id INT,
  result_status VARCHAR(50)
)

  robot_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  status VARCHAR(50),
  last_update TIMESTAMP
)
